# Laplace main site — environment configuration.
# Copy to `.env` and adjust. Every var is OPTIONAL — sensible devnet defaults are baked in,
# so the app runs against the live devnet programs out of the box.

# Cluster: localnet | devnet | mainnet-beta   (default: devnet)
VITE_CLUSTER=devnet

# RPC endpoint override. If unset, the cluster's default from @laplace-one/registry is used
# (devnet -> https://api.devnet.solana.com). The public endpoint works but is rate-limited
# and throttles getProgramAccounts, which the console uses for client-side discovery when no
# indexer is configured. For reliable reads + websockets (the slot clock and sendAndConfirm),
# point at a dedicated provider:
#   Helius:  https://devnet.helius-rpc.com/?api-key=YOUR_KEY     (free tier, recommended)
#   Alchemy: https://solana-devnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_KEY
#   QuickNode / Triton / Ankr (https://rpc.ankr.com/solana_devnet) also work.
# VITE_RPC_URL=https://devnet.helius-rpc.com/?api-key=YOUR_KEY

# Indexer read API base URL. If unset, the console falls back to client-side
# getProgramAccounts via the SDK (heavier; the public RPC may throttle it). Run the indexer
# locally (`laplace-indexer` to ingest, `laplace-indexer-api` to serve; default port 8787)
# or host it, then set:
# VITE_INDEXER_URL=http://localhost:8787
